==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Courtesan
<hw>Cour"te*san</hw> <pr>(k?r"t?-z?n; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.  <ets>courtisane</ets>, fr. <ets>courtisan</ets> courtier, It.  <ets>cortigiano</ets>; or directly fr. It.  <ets>cortigiana</ets>, or Sp.  <ets>cortesana</ets>. See <er>Court</er>.]</ety> <def>A woman who prostitutes herself for hire; a prostitute; a harlot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lasciviously decked like a <qex>courtesan</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir H. Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Courtesanship</ent>⟦br⟧
